column2:
This update is long overdue. It's been nearly two months now since I've moved into my new apartment. Not surprisingly, it feels like it's been about half that long. The summer is flying by in its usual manner. Despite it being as long as it has been, the past week I've <strong>finally </strong>finished up my room, by which I mean I put things on the wall and made it feel a bit more... lived in. In any case, I'll let some pictures do the talking. Here's our new place! We're on South Union St, about a 3 minute bike ride from Church St./downtown. Quiet neighborhood, gorgeous back porch with a fantastic view of the lake thanks to recently cut down trees. Big grassy backyard, flourishing vegetable garden and planters full of herbs.

